answers.body_markdown:
Your code `$cookie = $this-&gt;request-&gt;getCookie(&#39;persistence_key&#39;)` returns the cookie value, not the cookie itself. So you pass the cookie value to the `withExpiredCookie()` method instead of the cookie name. And anyway, passing the cookie name is now deprecated.

Something like this should work:

    $cookie = new Cookie(&#39;persistence_key&#39;);
    $this-&gt;response = $this-&gt;response-&gt;withExpiredCookie($cookie);

Please note that the cookie path must also correspond to how you create your cookie. As I have many CakePHP application on localhost, I tend to specifiy the cookie path when I create cookies:

    $cookie = new Cookie(&#39;my-cookie&#39;);
    $cookie = $cookie-&gt;withPath(Router::url(&#39;/&#39;));

So I have to destruct them like this:

    $cookie = new Cookie(&#39;my-cookie&#39;);
    $cookie = $cookie-&gt;withPath(Router::url(&#39;/&#39;));
    $this-&gt;response = $this-&gt;response-&gt;withExpiredCookie($cookie);

